Liz has posted a link in our show notes with a tweet that expresses some concerns about the ConZealand programme and an open letter to ConZealand outlining and detailing those concerns.

277
00:16:26,660 --> 00:16:32,280
Liz, would you like to talk a little bit about what's going on here?

278
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:38,900
Yes, I mean, I just happened to see this tweet retweeted on my feed today with a link to the open letter.

279
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:46,520
The discussion seems to be about essentially Hugo finalists and the use of Hugo finalists on the ConZealand programme.

280
00:16:47,080 --> 00:17:03,240
And it sounds like quite a lot of Hugo finalists have not really been offered things that are relevant to their expertise or they feel their panels do not have a diverse enough participants or a diverse enough framing of the topic of the panel.

281
00:17:03,660 --> 00:17:13,280
